  <bioghist id="aspace_36f47b8ea0b301e45b56ccd60501f559">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Gustav Kappler, Cornell University Class of 1961, M.D. 1965, was a vascular surgeon during the Vietnam War.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_a187c25fb457dc3b32092548c8108de4">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Includes color slides, with a tape recording and transcript describing the slides, 1984; also a DVD of a presentation by Dr. Kappler and David Leeser given at Weill Auditorium on February 13, 2012 and a DVD with a Powerpoint presentation of the slides. Also tapes sent home, telegrams, and correspondence, 1970-1984; photograph album; Vietnamese currency and other memorabilia; and manuscript draft for article.</p><p>Booklet compiled for the 2008 Reunion of staff from the Phu Bai/85th Evacuation Hospital, 1971/72, with information about their later lives. Folder of materials from the 2010 Reunion, including updates on their lives, CDs with photographs and songs, and information about Hilton Head.</p>  </scopecontent>
